<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb92ad5b0-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s1651"><num value="1651">§ 1651.</num><heading> Piracy under law of nations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever, on the high seas, commits the crime of piracy as defined by the law of nations, and is afterwards brought into or found in the United States, shall be imprisoned for life.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb92ad5b1-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/774">62 Stat. 774</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
